Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine light pink-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Production date: 152BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Pausanias No parallel for the secondary stamp in M. Palaczyk, 'Die Zusatzstempel ('secondary stamps') der rhodischen Amphoren', ÖJh 68 (1999) 59-103. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0962)
